  <Name>k__BackingField: 1 Thessalonians
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 1th
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from PaulThe Faith of the Thessalonian Believers
      content: '  This letter is from Paul, Silas,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Timothy.We are
        writing to the church in Thessalonica, to you who belong to God the Father
        and the Lord Jesus Christ.May God give you grace and peace.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Silvanus, </b>the Greek form of the name.
    - title: 
      content: 'We always thank God for all of you and pray for you constantly. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As we pray to our God and Father about you, we think of your faithful
        work, your loving deeds, and the enduring hope you have because of our Lord
        Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We know, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] that God loves
        you and has chosen you to be his own people. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For when we brought you the Good News, it was not only with words
        but also with power, for the Holy Spirit gave you full assurance[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that what we said was true. And you know of our concern for you from the
        way we lived when we were with you. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: Or <b>with the power of the Holy Spirit, so you can have full assurance.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So you received the message with joy from the Holy Spirit in spite
        of the severe suffering it brought you. In this way, you imitated both us
        and the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As a result, you have become an example to all the believers in Greece\u2014throughout
        both Macedonia and Achaia.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: <b>Macedonia </b>and <b>Achaia </b>were the northern and southern
          regions of Greece.
    - title: 
      content: "And now the word of the Lord is ringing out from you to people everywhere,
        even beyond Macedonia and Achaia, for wherever we go we find people telling
        us about your faith in God. We don\u2019t need to tell them about it, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for they keep talking about the wonderful welcome you gave us and
        how you turned away from idols to serve the living and true God. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Paul Remembers His Visit
      content: '  You yourselves know, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] that
        our visit to you was not a failure. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 2:9, 14, 17.
    - title: 
      content: 'You know how badly we had been treated at Philippi just before we
        came to you and how much we suffered there. Yet our God gave us the courage
        to declare his Good News to you boldly, in spite of great opposition. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you can see we were not preaching with any deceit or impure motives
        or trickery.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we speak as messengers approved by God to be entrusted with the
        Good News. Our purpose is to please God, not people. He alone examines the
        motives of our hearts. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never once did we try to win you with flattery, as you well know.
        And God is our witness that we were not pretending to be your friends just
        to get your money! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As for human praise, we have never sought it from you or anyone else.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As apostles of Christ we certainly had a right to make some demands
        of you, but instead we were like children[[COMMENT(0)]] among you. Or we
        were like a mother feeding and caring for her own children. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>we were gentle.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "We loved you so much that we shared with you not only God\u2019s
        Good News but our own lives, too.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you remember, dear brothers and sisters, how hard we worked
        among you? Night and day we toiled to earn a living so that we would not
        be a burden to any of you as we preached God\u2019s Good News to you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You yourselves are our witnesses\u2014and so is God\u2014that we
        were devout and honest and faultless toward all of you believers. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you know that we treated each of you as a father treats his own
        children. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We pleaded with you, encouraged you, and urged you to live your lives
        in a way that God would consider worthy. For he called you to share in his
        Kingdom and glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, we never stop thanking God that when you received his
        message from us, you didn\u2019t think of our words as mere human ideas.
        You accepted what we said as the very word of God\u2014which, of course,
        it is. And this word continues to work in you who believe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And then, dear brothers and sisters, you suffered persecution from
        your own countrymen. In this way, you imitated the believers in God\u2019s
        churches in Judea who, because of their belief in Christ Jesus, suffered
        from their own people, the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For some of the Jews killed the prophets, and some even killed the
        Lord Jesus. Now they have persecuted us, too. They fail to please God and
        work against all humanity '
      comments: []
    - title: "Timothy\u2019s Good Report about the Church"
      content: 'as they try to keep us from preaching the Good News of salvation
        to the Gentiles. By doing this, they continue to pile up their sins. But
        the anger of God has caught up with them at last.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters, after we were separated from you for a
        little while (though our hearts never left you), we tried very hard to come
        back because of our intense longing to see you again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We wanted very much to come to you, and I, Paul, tried again and
        again, but Satan prevented us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After all, what gives us hope and joy, and what will be our proud
        reward and crown as we stand before our Lord Jesus when he returns? It is
        you! '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Finally, when we could stand it no longer, we decided to stay alone
        in Athens, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and we sent Timothy to visit you. He is our brother and God\u2019s
        co-worker[[COMMENT(0)]] in proclaiming the Good News of Christ. We sent him
        to strengthen you, to encourage you in your faith, "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: "Other manuscripts read <b>and God\u2019s servant; </b>still others
          read <b>and a co-worker, </b>or <b>and a servant and co-worker for God,
          </b>or <b>and God\u2019s servant and our co-worker.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'and to keep you from being shaken by the troubles you were going
        through. But you know that we are destined for such troubles. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even while we were with you, we warned you that troubles would soon
        come\u2014and they did, as you well know. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why, when I could bear it no longer, I sent Timothy to find
        out whether your faith was still strong. I was afraid that the tempter had
        gotten the best of you and that our work had been useless.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now Timothy has just returned, bringing us good news about your
        faith and love. He reports that you always remember our visit with joy and
        that you want to see us as much as we want to see you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we have been greatly encouraged in the midst of our troubles and
        suffering, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] because you have remained
        strong in your faith. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'It gives us new life to know that you are standing firm in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How we thank God for you! Because of you we have great joy as we
        enter God\u2019s presence. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Night and day we pray earnestly for you, asking God to let us see
        you again to fill the gaps in your faith.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May God our Father and our Lord Jesus bring us to you very soon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And may the Lord make your love for one another and for all people
        grow and overflow, just as our love for you overflows. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Live to Please God
      content: '  Finally, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] we urge you in
        the name of the Lord Jesus to live in a way that pleases God, as we have
        taught you. You live this way already, and we encourage you to do so even
        more. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 4:10, 13.
    - title: 
      content: 'For you remember what we taught you by the authority of the Lord
        Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God\u2019s will is for you to be holy, so stay away from all sexual
        sin. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then each of you will control his own body[[COMMENT(0)]] and live
        in holiness and honor\u2014 "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Or <b>will know how to take a wife for himself; </b>or <b>will learn
          to live with his own wife; </b>Greek reads <b>will know how to possess
          his own vessel.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'not in lustful passion like the pagans who do not know God and his
        ways. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never harm or cheat a fellow believer in this matter by violating
        his wife,[[COMMENT(0)]] for the Lord avenges all such sins, as we have solemnly
        warned you before. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: Greek <b>Never harm or cheat a brother in this matter.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'God has called us to live holy lives, not impure lives. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, anyone who refuses to live by these rules is not disobeying
        human teaching but is rejecting God, who gives his Holy Spirit to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But we don\u2019t need to write to you about the importance of loving
        each other,[[COMMENT(0)]] for God himself has taught you to love one another. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: Greek <b>about brotherly love.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Indeed, you already show your love for all the believers[[COMMENT(0)]]
        throughout Macedonia. Even so, dear brothers and sisters, we urge you to
        love them even more.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Greek <b>the brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Make it your goal to live a quiet life, minding your own business
        and working with your hands, just as we instructed you before. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Hope of the Resurrection
      content: 'Then people who are not believers will respect the way you live,
        and you will not need to depend on others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And now, dear brothers and sisters, we want you to know what will
        happen to the believers who have died[[COMMENT(0)]] so you will not grieve
        like people who have no hope. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: Greek <b>those who have fallen asleep; </b>also in 4:14.
    - title: 
      content: 'For since we believe that Jesus died and was raised to life again,
        we also believe that when Jesus returns, God will bring back with him the
        believers who have died.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We tell you this directly from the Lord: We who are still living
        when the Lord returns will not meet him ahead of those who have died.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:15 '
        content: Greek <b>those who have fallen asleep.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Lord himself will come down from heaven with a commanding
        shout, with the voice of the archangel, and with the trumpet call of God.
        First, the believers who have died[[COMMENT(0)]] will rise from their graves. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:16 '
        content: Greek <b>the dead in Christ.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, together with them, we who are still alive and remain on the
        earth will be caught up in the clouds to meet the Lord in the air. Then we
        will be with the Lord forever. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  Now concerning how and when all this will happen, dear brothers
        and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] we don\u2019t really need to write you. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 5:4, 12, 14, 25, 26, 27.
    - title: 
      content: "For you know quite well that the day of the Lord\u2019s return will
        come unexpectedly, like a thief in the night. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When people are saying, \u201CEverything is peaceful and secure,\u201D
        then disaster will fall on them as suddenly as a pregnant woman\u2019s labor
        pains begin. And there will be no escape.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you aren\u2019t in the dark about these things, dear brothers
        and sisters, and you won\u2019t be surprised when the day of the Lord comes
        like a thief.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:4 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>comes upon you as if you were thieves.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For you are all children of the light and of the day; we don\u2019t
        belong to darkness and night. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So be on your guard, not asleep like the others. Stay alert and be
        clearheaded. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Night is the time when people sleep and drinkers get drunk. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But let us who live in the light be clearheaded, protected by the
        armor of faith and love, and wearing as our helmet the confidence of our
        salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God chose to save us through our Lord Jesus Christ, not to pour
        out his anger on us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Christ died for us so that, whether we are dead or alive when he
        returns, we can live with him forever. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Advice"
      content: 'So encourage each other and build each other up, just as you are
        already doing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dear brothers and sisters, honor those who are your leaders in the
        Lord\u2019s work. They work hard among you and give you spiritual guidance. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Show them great respect and wholehearted love because of their work.
        And live peacefully with each other.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Brothers and sisters, we urge you to warn those who are lazy. Encourage
        those who are timid. Take tender care of those who are weak. Be patient with
        everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See that no one pays back evil for evil, but always try to do good
        to each other and to all people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Always be joyful. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never stop praying. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Be thankful in all circumstances, for this is God\u2019s will for
        you who belong to Christ Jesus.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not stifle the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not scoff at prophecies, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but test everything that is said. Hold on to what is good. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Greetings"
      content: 'Stay away from every kind of evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now may the God of peace make you holy in every way, and may your
        whole spirit and soul and body be kept blameless until our Lord Jesus Christ
        comes again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God will make this happen, for he who calls you is faithful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters, pray for us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet all the brothers and sisters with a sacred kiss.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I command you in the name of the Lord to read this letter to all
        the brothers and sisters.  '
      comments: []
